Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Peel @Carrots{4}(peeled and cut on an angle) into ½-inch-thick pieces. In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Herbes de Provence{1%tsp}, half the @Honey{1/2%oz}, and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with plenty of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Add carrots and toss to coat.

Arrange carrots on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until browned and tender, about ~{20%minutes}. Meanwhile, cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into evenly sized cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with @salt{} water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Once done, drain well and set aside.

Meanwhile, trim, then thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced), separating greens and whites. Pat @Rib-Eye Steak{20%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season generously all over with @salt{generously} and @pepper{generously}. Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steaks and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Remove steaks from pan and set aside to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out any browned bits from pan with a paper towel. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1}(peeled and minced) until you have 2 TBSP. Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for steaks over medium heat. Add minced shallot and cook until just softened, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @Beef Demi-Glace{1} and ⅓ cup @water{1/3%cup}. Simmer until slightly thickened, about ~{1%minute}.

Stir @Butter{1%tbsp} and any juices released by steaks into pan. Remove from heat and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Once carrots are done roasting, drizzle with remaining @Honey{} and sprinkle with @Chili Flakes{1%tsp} to taste.

Place pot used for potatoes over low heat. Add @Butter{1%tbsp} and scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until scallions are slightly softened, about ~{1%minute}.

Add potatoes to pot and mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Stir in @Sour Cream{6%tbsp}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Slice steaks against the grain. Divide carrots, potatoes, and steaks between plates. Spoon pan sauce over steaks and potatoes. Garnish with scallion greens.